<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="297" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1223,1489]" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">
<taxonomicName box="[199,304,1293,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Brypoctia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,304,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">Brypoctia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed to include 
<taxonomicName authority="Dyar, 1910" authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1910" box="[586,901,1292,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Xyleutes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigifer">
<emphasis box="[586,770,1292,1316]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="297">Xyleutes strigifer</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dyar" box="[780,901,1292,1315]" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" refString="Dyar, H. G. (1910) Descriptions of some new species and genera of Lepidoptera from Mexico. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 38 (1742), 229 ‾ 273." type="journal article" year="1910">Dyar, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
based on the unique structural characters of the head appendages and thoracic sclerites (
<bibRefCitation author="Schoorl" box="[579,727,1327,1350]" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" refString="Schoorl, J. W. (1990) A phylogenetic study on Cossidae (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia) based on external adult morphology. Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 263, 1 ‾ 295." type="journal article" year="1990">Schoorl 1990</bibRefCitation>
). As mentioned by Schoorl, “male antenna bipectinate for approx. 0.4 times its length, labial palpi slender and approx. 0.5 times length of eye-diameter, second segment of labial palpi apically slightly thickened, tegula ventroposteriorly bluntly pointed (
<bibRefCitation author="Schoorl" box="[907,1059,1396,1419]" pageId="0" pageNumber="297" refString="Schoorl, J. W. (1990) A phylogenetic study on Cossidae (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia) based on external adult morphology. Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 263, 1 ‾ 295." type="journal article" year="1990">Schoorl 1990</bibRefCitation>
)”. Other characters refer to minor details of the thorax which are impossible to distinguish in field determinations and require examination using a microscope.
</paragraph>
